<DocsLayout title="Runs & Monitoring">
  <h1>Runs & Monitoring</h1>
  <p class="text-lg text-slate-400">Track execution history, logs, and errors for all your data jobs.</p>

  <h2>Overview</h2>
  <p>A <strong>run</strong> is a single execution of an upload, transformation, or pipeline. Every time a job is triggered — manually or by a schedule — a run record is created to track its progress, outcome, and logs.</p>

  <h3>Properties</h3>
  <table>
    <thead><tr><th>Field</th><th>Description</th></tr></thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr><td><code>target</code></td><td>The upload, transformation, or pipeline that was executed</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>status</code></td><td>Current state of the run (see below)</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>started_at</code></td><td>When execution began</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>finished_at</code></td><td>When execution completed (or failed)</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>rows_loaded</code></td><td>Number of rows processed (for uploads)</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>logs</code></td><td>Full execution logs (streamed in real-time)</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>error_message</code></td><td>Error details if the run failed</td></tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>

  <h2>Statuses</h2>
  <table>
    <thead><tr><th>Status</th><th>Description</th></tr></thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr><td><code>pending</code></td><td>Run is queued, waiting for a worker</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>running</code></td><td>Execution is in progress</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>success</code></td><td>Run completed without errors</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>failed</code></td><td>Run encountered an error</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>cancelled</code></td><td>Run was manually cancelled</td></tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>

  <h2>Run History</h2>
  <p>The run history view lets you filter and browse all past executions:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>Filter by <strong>status</strong> (success, failed, etc.)</li>
    <li>Filter by <strong>target type</strong> (upload, transformation, pipeline)</li>
    <li>Filter by <strong>date range</strong></li>
    <li>View <strong>streaming logs</strong> in real-time for running jobs</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Example</h3>
  <pre><code>Run #1247
Target: Upload → "Sync Stripe data"
Status: success
Started: 2026-03-10 02:00:03 UTC
Finished: 2026-03-10 02:03:47 UTC
Duration: 3m 44s
Rows loaded: 15,832</code></pre>

  <h2>How to monitor and manage runs</h2>
  <ol class="list-decimal pl-6 space-y-2">
    <li>Navigate to <strong>Runs</strong> in the sidebar to see all execution history</li>
    <li>Use the <strong>Status</strong> filter to show only <code>success</code>, <code>failed</code>, <code>running</code>, or <code>pending</code> runs</li>
    <li>Use the <strong>Target type</strong> filter to narrow down to uploads, transformations, or pipelines</li>
    <li>Click on a run row to expand <strong>Logs</strong> — logs stream in real-time for running jobs</li>
    <li>For failed runs, check the <strong>Error</strong> column for a summary and the logs for the full stack trace</li>
    <li>To re-run a failed job, go back to the source (upload/transformation/pipeline) and click <strong>Run</strong></li>
  </ol>

  <h2>Error Handling & Retries</h2>
  <p>When a run fails:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>The full error message and stack trace are captured in the run logs</li>
    <li>The run status is set to <code>failed</code></li>
    <li>If notifications are configured, team members are alerted</li>
    <li>Failed runs can be retried manually from the UI</li>
  </ul>
</DocsLayout>
